00:04:59.610 --> 00:05:05.610
She said, thanks to JW.org, nothing in the hall seemed strange to me.

00:05:05.610 --> 00:05:09.610
The program, the people, all of it was familiar.

00:05:09.610 --> 00:05:14.610
After she attended meetings for a month, she asked for a Bible study.

00:05:14.610 --> 00:05:17.610
So she was careful, but she got the truth.

00:05:17.610 --> 00:05:22.610
And her first encounter after that man was our website.

00:05:22.610 --> 00:05:27.610
Dregan was a Franciscan monk in Slovenia.

00:05:27.610 --> 00:05:30.610
He'd been in the order for a number of years, but there was something missing.

00:05:30.610 --> 00:05:32.610
There was a void in his life.

00:05:32.610 --> 00:05:37.610
He realized that his religion was not satisfying his spiritual need.

00:05:37.610 --> 00:05:43.610
So he went online and he joined a chat room with a bunch of evangelicals.

00:05:43.610 --> 00:05:49.610
Well, as you can imagine, eventually some negative comments were made about Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:05:49.610 --> 00:05:51.610
Did that stop Dregan?

00:05:51.610 --> 00:05:52.610
No.

00:05:52.610 --> 00:05:55.610
Another fear-minded person.

00:05:55.610 --> 00:06:01.610
He thought it's not fair to criticize Jehovah's Witnesses when, thankfully,

00:06:01.610 --> 00:06:04.610
none of Jehovah's Witnesses are in that chat room.

00:06:04.610 --> 00:06:12.610
So he went online and found her website, and he was delighted with the quality of the website.

00:06:12.610 --> 00:06:17.610
Now he was a monk, and in the Franciscan order, that particular Franciscan order,

00:06:17.610 --> 00:06:22.610
the monks were only allowed to leave the monastery on Mondays.

00:06:22.610 --> 00:06:27.610
So one day he found the address of the branch office in Slovenia,

00:06:27.610 --> 00:06:30.610
and a Monday morning he went to the branch and got a tour.

00:06:30.610 --> 00:06:33.610
And the brothers received him very warmly.

00:06:33.610 --> 00:06:40.610
He was very impressed with what he saw, and he came away with a novel idea.

00:06:40.610 --> 00:06:46.610
He came away with the thought that he should be reading the Bible every day.

00:06:46.610 --> 00:06:52.610
And so he went back to the monastery, went online, and started reading the Bible online every day.

00:06:52.610 --> 00:06:56.610
His fellow monks observed this, and they thought this was hilarious.

00:06:56.610 --> 00:06:59.610
What's the Catholic monk doing reading the Bible?

00:06:59.610 --> 00:07:02.610
But he didn't allow their opposition to deter him.

00:07:02.610 --> 00:07:07.610
He kept reading the Bible, and then kept consulting JW.org,

00:07:07.610 --> 00:07:14.610
and he realized on consulting the website that the memorial that year was on a Monday.

00:07:14.610 --> 00:07:21.610
So he was going to be able to attend, and he did, and that did it.

00:07:21.610 --> 00:07:23.610
That meeting.

