00:09:29.620 --> 00:09:34.620
But I think what has really opened the eyes of the brothers and our Bible students

00:09:34.620 --> 00:09:40.620
to the organization has been JW Broadcasting and JW.org.

00:09:40.620 --> 00:09:45.620
And you see now as you go from one congregation to another or one circuit to another

00:09:45.620 --> 00:09:50.620
that the brothers are really talking about the organization as they never did before.

00:09:50.620 --> 00:09:56.620
So it's obvious that technology has contributed to the understanding of the brothers

00:09:56.620 --> 00:09:59.620
and to the spread of the good news.

00:09:59.620 --> 00:10:01.620
Now, here's a warning.

00:10:01.620 --> 00:10:04.620
Technology has a place.

00:10:04.620 --> 00:10:06.620
It has a big place.

00:10:06.620 --> 00:10:08.620
But there is a danger.

00:10:08.620 --> 00:10:11.620
Have you ever heard the term fubbing?

00:10:11.620 --> 00:10:13.620
Fubbing?

00:10:13.620 --> 00:10:16.620
P-H-U-B-B-I-N-G.

00:10:16.620 --> 00:10:21.620
It's a combination of foam and snubbing.

00:10:21.620 --> 00:10:27.620
And it refers to the act of ignoring real people while consulting an electronic device.

00:10:27.620 --> 00:10:30.620
So picture a man and a woman in a restaurant.

00:10:30.620 --> 00:10:32.620
And each one is online.

00:10:32.620 --> 00:10:37.620
Each one is consulting a different website or answering mail.

00:10:37.620 --> 00:10:40.620
And they're not talking to each other.

00:10:40.620 --> 00:10:44.620
It's a real problem, according to a study by Baylor University.

00:10:44.620 --> 00:10:49.620
So what we want to do is to stay connected, not just to the internet,

00:10:49.620 --> 00:10:54.620
but to stay connected to real people to those around us.

00:10:54.620 --> 00:10:59.620
A brother John Barr of the governing body used to say that if we shut out those around us

00:10:59.620 --> 00:11:05.620
while consulting an electronic device, we're really not focusing on the sounds of life.

00:11:05.620 --> 00:11:09.620
We are missing the sounds of life.

00:11:09.620 --> 00:11:15.620
And we're also missing out on opportunities to strengthen our bond with others.
